article.headline: Milwaukee 95, Ohio Dominican 80
article.story: MILWAUKEE -- Jordan Aaron scored 34 points and Milwaukee broke away from a close game in the second half to beat Ohio Dominican 95-80 on Saturday. Paris Gulley added 20 points and seven rebounds for Milwaukee (4-10), which led just 36-32 at halftime against the Division II school. Gulley's layup with 17:25 left made it 46-36 Milwaukee, and it held a double-figure lead nearly the entire half after that. Aaron was 9 for 15 from the field, including 4 of 8 from 3-point range, and made all 12 of his free throws. Demetrius Harris had 14 points, five rebounds and four blocked shots for the winners. James Haarsma added 12 points. Morgan Jones had 24 points and eight assists for Ohio Dominican (3-8), which has lost seven in a row.
